commit_message: Create LICENSE
Added support for recording the applied Extract Clone refactorings. Updated plug-in version to 5.0.68
Updated plug-in version to 5.0.67
Fixed overlapping text edits when multiple consecutive method declarations are removed.
Fixed erroneous pull up of additional methods called within the clones that already exist in the common superclass.

Fixed bug reported by Sven Peldszus in class MyAbstractStatement Method recurseDelegations() falls into infinite recursion when two methods delegate to each other. The bug was replicated in project Lucene 1.4.3 and class org.apache.lucene.analysis.Analyzer where methods public TokenStream tokenStream(String fieldName, Reader reader) public TokenStream tokenStream(Reader reader) delegate to each other.
Update README.md Added IEEE Software Blog post about JDeodorant's clone refactoring feature.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/tsantalis/JDeodorant

Fixed the detection of field rename (contains -> regexps) in duplicated methods org.apache.tools.ant.filters.LineContains::read() org.apache.tools.ant.filters.LineContainsRegExp::read() found in Apache Ant 1.7.0
Update README.md Added paper accepted at ICSE 2017.

Fixed the number of total opportunities reported for Feature Envy and the number of total groups reported for God Class. The new implementation does not have a separate result for the "current system" and thus we should not subtract -1
Added precondition containsNonAccessedFieldInExtractedClass() to eliminate candidates with extracted fields not accessed by the extracted methods.
-Added precondition validRemainingFieldsInSourceClass() -Extended precondition validRemainingMethodsInSourceClass() to check for method toString() -Fixed God Class visualization
Eliminated virtual application for Move Method and Extract Class candidate refactorings.
Removed P_ENABLE_CALL_GRAPH_ANALYSIS Preference
Checking for parameter type collision in the extracted methods.
Removed @Test annotation from the extracted methods so that they will not be considered as new tests by junit.
Improved ExtractClassRefactoring to handle properly statically imported methods in the extracted class.

Fixed the mapping of case jfreechart-1.0.10/tests/org/jfree/chart/annotations/junit/XYPolygonAnnotationTests.testCloning():void jfreechart-1.0.10/tests/org/jfree/chart/annotations/junit/CategoryPointerAnnotationTests.testCloning():void If the erasure type of the class instance creations are different, then the arguments of the class instance creations
are not compared, even if they have the same number of arguments.

Fix to avoid the addition of changed/added ICompilationUnits from the Eclipse Refactoring Wizard before the refactoring is actually applied on the source code. ElementChangedListener is converted to Singleton.

-Added containsNullCheckForTargetObject() precondition -Extended precondition targetClassContainsMethodWithSourceMethodSignature()
to handle the cases where the source method has the same parameter list
as a target method with an additional parameter of the target class type.
Removing redundant ASTSlice objects from ASTSliceGroup

Fixed the mapping of case 266-1-2 found in project Apache Ant 1.7.0 (Deckard results) org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.optional.clearcase.ClearCase.run(Commandline):int org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.optional.sos.SOS.run(Commandline):int
Made consistent the way findCloneMethod() is called in methods createCloneMethod() and updateCloneInSourceClass()

Using the same criteria to sort ControlDependenceTreeNodeMatchPair objects as in DivideAndConquerMatcher.findMaximumStateWithMinimumDifferences() the order of comparison criteria is:
1. getDistinctDifferenceCount()
2. getNonDistinctDifferenceCount()
3. getNonDistinctDifferenceCountIncludingTypeMismatches()
getNodeMappingRelativeIdDiff() and getEditDistanceOfDifferences()
are left for future implementation if deemed necessary.

Extended createCloneMethod() to create method clone() if it is not already declared in the source class, but it is inherited from a superclass.
Extended methods updateWriteObjectInSourceClass() updateReadObjectInSourceClass() to create methods writeObject() and readObject(), respectively if they are not already declared in the source class.
Extended Extract Class Refactoring to update method clone() so that it clones properly the reference to the extracted class.

-Removed precondition containsReadObjectMethodAssigningExtractedField() -Fixed method handleAccessedFieldNotHavingSetterMethod()
to replace properly the field accesses passed as parameters to the extracted methods
with a "this" prefix

-Extended Extract Class Refactoring
to update methods readObject() and writeObject()
so that they handle properly the reading and writing
of the field referring to the extracted class
from/to a stream.

-Extract Class candidates
containing one of the methods
readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream)
writeObject(java.io.ObjectOutputStream)
are automatically excluded.
Fix for issue #57

-Added precondition in Extract Class candidates to check if the source class contains method readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream) and it assigns a field to be extracted. -Disabled the precondition checking for serializable extracted fields.

-Fixed NoSuchElementException in methods
isFirstNonMappedNode() and isLastNonMappedNode()
Improved method findNonMappedNodes() to avoid moving mapped nodes to non-mapped nodes
if they are nested under an originally non-mapped node.

-Added support for postfix expressions in method modifyExtractedFieldAssignmentsInSourceClass() -Changed the logic of method setPublicModifierToSourceMethod()
to update protected access modifier only for methods
in classes belonging to a different package than the
package of the source/extracted class.

-Extended Extract Class refactoring implementation
to update the access modifier of methods declared in the superclass
of the source class containing the methods to be extracted.

-Fixed the addition of qualifier for statically accessed source fields
in the extracted class (UNITS.length was excluded from being qualified).

-Fixed the naming of the getter methods
created for source fields accessed in the extracted class,
when a source method has the same name.

-Renaming the arguments passed to recursive extracted method invocations
for the non-extracted source fields accessed in the extracted methods
with "this" prefix

-Renaming the parameters passed to the extracted methods
for the non-extracted source fields accessed in the extracted methods
with "this" prefix according to
createNameForParameterizedFieldAccess()

-Passing fields as parameters to extracted methods
with a "this" field access
to avoid name collisions with local variables.

-Added new precondition for Extract Class Refactoring The methods to be extracted should not access fields of the enclosing class e.g., SegmentedTimeline.this.segmentsIncluded -Fix to handle qualifiedNames being part of array expressions,
in which the rightmost part is an extracted field.

-Fixed the initializer of extracted fields
referencing a static field in the source class.

-The mapping of two statements is not allowed
if they both declare a variable,
but this variable is used in the mapped statements
of only one of the clone fragments.

Enabled the processing of class instance creations only for those assigned to variables. Introduced property isStatic to AbstractVariable. Fixed the caching of used/modified fields in internal method call analysis to store properly statically accessed fields. Extended rule movableBeforeFirstMappedNode() to include the cases where a mapped node modifies the state of an object that is used by a non-mapped node.

Fixed infinite recursion problem in method recurseDelegations() that occurs when the delegate method is the same as the delegator method. Bug occurred in project jgroups-2.10.0 and method org.jgroups.stack.Protocol.down(org.jgroups.Event):java.lang.Object

Extended the precondition checking whether it is possible to move unmapped statements or expressions in differences throwing exception(s), by including those nested under any control statement (before only those nested under a try block were excluded).

Complemented the rule incomingDataDependenciesFromUnvisitedNodes() with new rule incomingDataDependenciesFromNonMatchingNodes(), which checks whether a pair of nodes has incoming dependencies from a non-matching pair of nodes (i.e., nodes mapped with other nodes, but not with each other). This is a fix for several failing serialization tests, where changing the order of the mapped statements causes failures in deserialization.

Improved method getTypeBinding() to recover the actual typeBinding for NullLiteral objects, instead of returning null. This is achieved in the cases where the passed object is an argument of a method invocation or class instance creation.
Extended MethodCallAnalyzer to support the analysis of arguments passed in external method invocations.
Fixed NullPointerException in method exactSubType() occurring when the passed variableDeclaration parameter is null.
Reverted back to Java 1.5 compliance level.
Changed compliance to Java 1.7

-Generating a default value for the returned variable in the case of missing initialization. -All static fields being accessed in the type-checking code fragment, will be statically accessed after the refactoring using the name of the class they are declared in as the qualifier.

-Enabling the replacement of type field accesses in class instance creation arguments. -The static fields being accessed in the type-checking code fragment, will be statically accessed after the refactoring using the name of the class they are declared in as the qualifier. If a static field has a private access modifier, then the access modifier is updated to public.
Fixed typo is message "Compilation errors were detected in the project."

-Added Progress Monitor for buildProject() method in ASTReader. -Added new precondition for Long Method code smell. If the slice contains the declaration of a variable that is a stream and the stream is closed in the finally clause of a try statement, which is also included in the slice, then the refactoring opportunity is rejected. -Fixed generateRequiredImportDeclarationsBasedOnSignature() to include the return type of the typeCheckMethod when the returned variable is null. -Fixed precondition containsLocalVariableAssignment() to take into account postfix and prefix expressions updating local variables.

-Added new precondition for Long Method code smell. If the variable criterion is a stream whose declaration is included in the slice, and the stream is closed in the finally clause of a try statement, which is also included in the slice, then the refactoring opportunity is rejected. -In ExtractMethodFragmentRefactoring.getThrownExceptionTypes(Statement) class instance creations are also examined for thrown exception types. -In ExtractMethodFragmentRefactoring.tryBlockCatchesExceptionType(TryStatement, ITypeBinding) the passed exception type as parameter is also checked if it is a subType of the of the exception types caught in the catch clauses of the TryStatement. -In MethodCallAnalyzer.handleAlreadyAnalyzedMethod() the thrown exception types are no longer recursively obtained. Only the thrown exception types in the first-level method calls or class instance creations are taken into account.

If the user has opened multiple code smell views, and each one of them contains refactoring opportunities for a different project, then a change to one of projects will disable the "Apply Refactoring" button only for the code smell view corresponding to the changed project.

Improved the views for Feature Envy, God Class, Long Method, Type-Checking by allowing the user to apply refactoring opportunities on the currently examined project, even if the user has selected another project in between. The active project is always the last project on which a detection of code smells has been performed.

The Extract Method refactoring opportunities in which the statement declaring the variable criterion is nested in a deeper level compared to the level in which the extracted method invocation will be placed (i.e., the level in which the first statement of the slice is nested) are automatically excluded from being reported.

-When creating the method call graph, the methods that simply throw the UnsupportedOperationException are considered as abstract implementations, and thus the overriding methods in the subclasses are analyzed. -The ExtractedMethodInvocationInsertionNode is the first node from the set of removable nodes (not the first node from the set of slice nodes) -Files generated by the JJTree preprocessor are automatically skipped from the analysis for refactoring opportunities.

-The project is always being built before getting parsed. If compilation errors are detected, then CompilationErrorDetectedException is thrown and systemObject is not created. -Files generated by Parser generators are automatically skipped from the analysis for refactoring opportunities. Currently, JavaCC, ANTLR, JFlex, and CUP generators are supported.

Setting public access modifier to source class methods being called in the extracted class through a reference to the source class. This is a fix for the refactoring opportunity found in class net.sourceforge.cobertura.instrument.Main of project cobertura-1.9.4.1

Fixed the initialization of final fields inside the constructor of the extracted class, which use variables declared inside the constructor of the source class. This is a fix for the refactoring opportunity found in class net.sourceforge.cobertura.reporting.xml.XMLReport of project cobertura-1.9.4.1

If the parent expression of a field access is a qualified name, then the field access is replaced with a call to the corresponding getter method in the extracted class. other.lock.tryLock(); => other.getLock().tryLock(); this.lock.tryLock(); => sourceClassParameter.getLock().tryLock();
Replaced obsolete code for the generation of a type from a typeBinding with a call to RefactoringUtility.generateTypeFromTypeBinding()

-In Extract Class Refactoring, the fields being inherited by the source class and used in the extracted methods are properly handled. This is a fix for the refactoring opportunities found in the following classes of project cobertura-1.9.4.1 net.sourceforge.cobertura.coveragedata.ProjectData net.sourceforge.cobertura.coveragedata.SourceFileData net.sourceforge.cobertura.coveragedata.PackageData net.sourceforge.cobertura.coveragedata.ClassData -Fixed the case where a compound assignment operator is applied on an extracted field within a non-extracted method.
This is a fix for the refactoring opportunity (contain+instrument+info) found in class net.sourceforge.cobertura.coveragedata.ClassData of project cobertura-1.9.4.1
The compound assignment operator that exists in method merge(CoverageData) is the following
this.containsInstrumentationInfo |= classData.containsInstrumentationInfo;

-In Extract Class refactoring a getter method for an extracted field is created only if this field is accessed by non-extracted methods in the source class. Respectively, a setter method for an extracted field is created only if this field is modified by non-extracted methods in the source class. -Fixed in Extract Class Refactoring the instantiation of source class static member types created inside the extracted methods.

-Fixed method FieldObject.generateFieldInstruction() to pass the variableBindingKey to the created field instruction object. -Improved method PDGNode.processArgumentsOfInternalClassInstanceCreation() to avoid the analysis of methods declared in local types (i.e., types declared inside a method and are not nested types) in addition to methods declared in anonymous classes. -Improved method CFGBranchNode.getImmediatelyNestedNodesFromAST() to handle blocks nested within control statements.
Improved the mapping process to prevent the mapping of statements being nested in the same level, but belonging to different basic blocks.

-Fixed the proper matching of if/else statement with a conditional expression (ternary operator) -Added a weight to METHOD_INVOCATION_NAME_MISMATCH differences equal to the Levenshtein distance of the method identifiers. -Improved the computation of weight for ARGUMENT_NUMBER_MISMATCH differences to take into account the case where one of the method calls has zero arguments.

-In Feature Envy code smell the source methods belonging to test classes are excluded from being reported as refactoring opportunities. -In DuplicatedCode view the ApplyRefactoring action is removed, because it is redundant -CloneGroupList maintains a reference to the imported Java Project to avoid the problems caused when the user is selecting another project and then returns back to the original imported project. -Updated plug-in version to 5.0.45
Avoid storing repeated and class-level clones in the CloneGroupList
Added legend to the DuplicatedCode view

Aligned master branch with JLS8 branch. OPERATOR_MISMATCH differences are effective only if they appear in expressions which are the direct conditional expression of if statements. Plug-in version updated to 5.0.43

The rule defined for onlyVariableTypeMismatchDifferences() is adjusted to tolerate also SUBCLASS_TYPE_MISMATCH differences. This is a fix for the following case found in JFreeChart-1.0.10 org.jfree.chart.renderer.category.AbstractCategoryItemRenderer.equals() org.jfree.chart.renderer.xy.AbstractXYItemRenderer.equals() Extended the rule incomingDataDependenciesFromUnvisitedNodes() to exclude the data dependencies coming from unmapped statements, if the statement that declares the variable of the data dependence is mapped.
This is a fix for the following case found in JFreeChart-1.0.10
org.jfree.chart.entity.junit.CategoryLabelEntityTests.testEquals()
org.jfree.chart.entity.junit.ContourEntityTests.testEquals()
Created a field for the ElementChangedListener, so that it can be unregistered when the view is disposed.

DuplicatedCode view part is updated To show clones with shifted offsets and tampered clones (i.e., clones
that no longer exist or have been edited)

Added 6 new methods in CompositeStatementObject to retrieve information from the expressions of the composite statements. If the control variable is a field, the last statement that modifies the field before the loop is added to the additional fragments.
Disabling binding resolution when parsing ASTs during the importing of clone detection results.

Added a fix to avoid NullPointerException in the case where an internal method call does not correspond to an existing method declaration. It happens for built-in enumeration methods, such as values() and valueOf() Added method getNestingDepth() in AbstractStatement
Replaced field String originClassName with TypeObject originClassType in class AbstractMethodInvocationObject.
Excluding the analysis of anonymous class declarations from the external constructor calls.
Fixed the previous commit to enable the analysis of external constructor calls.

Fixed NullPointerException in processArgumentsOfInternalClassInstanceCreation() taking place when the default constructor is called, but no such constructor declaration exists in the actual source code.
Fixed the update of 'return this;' statements in ExtractClassRefactoring. In all code smell views the involved files are opened in the editor before the Refactoring wizard to enable the Undo history.

Extended ComplicationUnitCache to support the caching of information related to constructor declarations. Extended AbstractMethodFragment to store the variables assigned with class instance creations. This will be used to set properly the sets of defined and used variables when a class is instantiated. Extended MethodCallAnalyzer to process internal static method calls. All PDGNode subclasses and PDGExpression have been extended to call method processArgumentsOfInternalClassInstanceCreation() for every class instance creation. This was a fix for case 1219|1-3 found in JFreeChart-1.0.10 (Deckard results) org.jfree.data.time.junit.MonthTests.testGetFirstMillisecond() org.jfree.data.time.junit.QuarterTests.testGetFirstMillisecond()

Extended preconditions controlParentExaminesVariableUsedInNonMappedNode() and controlParentExaminesVariableUsedInDifferenceExpression() to include as control parents the if statements containing a throw statement, which are placed before the non-mapped node or the node containing the difference expression, respectively. Method controlParentExaminesVariableInCondition() is called with 'false' for the excludeVariablesFoundInDifferences argument.

Moved the code for computing the return type of the extracted method from ExtractCloneRefactoring to PreconditionExaminer. Added clone-fragment-level precondition violation for the case where not all possible execution flows end in a return statement. Extended the previous implementation of precondition checkIfAllPossibleExecutionFlowsEndInReturn()

Extended preconditions controlParentExaminesVariableUsedInNonMappedNode() and controlParentExaminesVariableUsedInDifferenceExpression() to include as control parents the if statements containing a conditional return, which are placed before the non-mapped node or the node containing the difference expression, respectively. This is a fix for case 589|1-2 found in JFreeChart-1.0.10 (Deckard results) org.jfree.chart.plot.XYPlot.drawDomainMarkers() org.jfree.chart.plot.XYPlot.drawRangeMarkers()
Avoid NPE when cloneGroupList is null due to any exception in parsing
Used getEndOffset() method in CloneInstance class
Fixed the end offset bug in the constructor of CloneInstanceLocationInfo And some clean-ups
Bundle-Version is increased by one

Skip clone groups which have only one clone This may happen for instance when the ICompilationUnit cannot be found
for some of the clones in the clone group.
Throw InvalidInputFileException for ConQAT parser When there is no clone groups
Throw InvalidInputFileException in CCFinder when there is no clone group

Fixed the problem with CloneDROutputParser when we had parse exceptions The parser mistakenly stopped when we had parse exceptions (e.g.
ICompilationUnitNotFound exceptions)

Remove link styles for non-existing clone groups in the TreeViewer If a clone group is a subclone of another clone group, but the latter
does not exist in the TreeViewer (because it is either a repeated or
class-level clone), the link to this clone group will be disabled in the
corresponding column.
Fixed CCFinder output parser for literal tokens The problem was found in Group 806 in Apache Ant project
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/tsantalis/JDeodorant.git

Reversed again the order that the dependencies are examined (first incoming dependencies, then outgoing dependencies). This change fixes the mapping of statements in the following case found in JFreeChart 1.0.14 org.jfree.chart.renderer.category.LineAndShapeRenderer.getLegendItem() org.jfree.chart.renderer.category.ScatterRenderer.getLegendItem()

Fixed Overlapping TextEdits exception taking place when the clones belong to the same compilation unit and contribute the same import statement. Fixed NullPointerException occurring when calling method resolveConstructorBinding() over a ClassInstanceCreation using the diamond operator introduced in Java 7, e.g., new HashMap<>()
Removed redundant println
Added containsCloneGroup() method to CloneGroupList
TreeChain should contain only the ifParents and elseIfChildren inside the subTreeCDTNodes.
Removed unnecessary space
Showing meaningful warning to users when ICompilationUnit is not found
Removed unnecessary dependency
Added getEndOffset() to CloneInstanceLocationInfo
Added right-click support for refactoring and textual diff
Fixed getActualCodeFragment() method, based on substring
Added subclone information to the duplicated code TreeViewer

Added a check to prevent the mapping of statements having incoming data dependencies from unvisited statements, as long as the number of nodes from the two clone fragments (in which the search is restricted) is equal. This is a fix for case 178|1-2 from NiCad results in project JFreeChart-1.0.10
org.jfree.chart.renderer.category.BoxAndWhiskerRenderer.drawHorizontalItem()
org.jfree.chart.renderer.category.BoxAndWhiskerRenderer.drawVerticalItem()

Updated match(MethodInvocation, Object) to return directly when a static and a non-static method calls are being compared, only when the direct parents of the compared method calls are statements.

Reverted the computation of weight in BindingSignaturePair to fix case 480|1-2 from Deckard results in project JFreeChart-1.0.10
org.jfree.chart.axis.junit.LogAxisTests.testTranslateJava2DToValue()
org.jfree.chart.axis.junit.NumberAxisTests.testTranslateJava2DToValue()
Introduced constant JLS in class ASTReader. Replaced all uses of AST.JLS4 in the project with the constant ASTReader.JLS
Merge branch 'CloneImport'

Implemented CCFinder parser Pulled up formatPath() method from CloneDROutputParser so it can be
reused. The change in the super class is committed in the previous
commit
Fixed NPE when NodeFinder cannot find the expected node This mostly happens when there is a problem with offsets
Point directory dialog to the last selected folder (for CCFinder)
Removed the use of Path.toPosix
Added InvalidInputFileException for handling corresponding cases
Added support for CloneDR
Updated the UI
Added ConQAT parser (Supporting version 2015.2 of ConQAT)

Reversed the order that the dependencies are examined (first outgoing dependencies, then incoming dependencies). OPERATOR_MISMATCH is no longer considered as a typeMismatch in accordance to JLS8-support branch. Checking for NullPointerException in DuplicatedCode view taking place when the user clicks on the Cancel button of the CloneImport wizard.
Setting the parent CloneGroup for the CloneGroupInstance
Added support for NiCad output
Added getCloneGroupsCount() method
Added new Constructor for accepting a Throwable
Migrated the code for clone fragment refactoring to the IDE.
Added the original iMethod signature as a field in CloneInstance
Minimized memory usage by removing unnecessary fields from Clone objects
Fixed the issue for converting line numbers to offsets
Extended the functionality of the DuplicatedCode view to display the clone group and highlight the clones in the editor on doubleClick action
Added progress bar for parsing clone detector results
Updated ProgressObserver to notify about the current clone group index.
Added sample code to UI classes for using clone detector output parsers
Added functionality for parsing clone detector output files For the moment, we only support Deckard.
Fixed NullPointerException after calling FileDialog.open()
Updated the UI of the ImportClonesWizardPage
Exported Package ca.concordia.jdeodorant.clone.parsers
Added CloneDetectorType enum
Added the basic functionality for importing clones from clone detection tool results.

Extended MethodCallAnalyzer to process external static method calls. Extended MethodCallAnalyzer and Indexer to store the exception types of throw statements found in external method calls. Null literal type cannot be matched with a primitive type. The catch clause exception types are updated in the extracted method when there is a subclass type mismatch.
Adding check that methods with equalSignatureIgnoringSubclassTypeDifferences should be static in method allAccessedLocalMethodsHaveMatchingSignatures()

Made a distinction between direct and indirect local method calls within the clone fragments. If at least one of the access modifiers of two commonly accessed methods is protected, then method pulled up method is assigned with a protected modifier.

-Adding a remainingNode to statementsToBeMovedBefore only if remainingNode.getId() > removableNodes.first().getId() -Extended ASTNodeMatcher to reduce the weight of TYPE_COMPATIBLE_REPLACEMENT differences that are reversed from previous differences appearing in the arguments of method calls and class instance creations. Now both reversed arguments are set with a weight equal to 1. -Extended rule extractToUtilityClass() to return true if at least one of the methods containing the clone fragments is static. -Improvement in the detection of commonly passed parameters. The variables appearing only in differences are excluded from being matched as commonly passed parameters.

Extended matchingVariableDifference() to consider differences in variable types too. The precondition controlParentExaminesVariableInCondition() excludes the variables found in differences when it is called by controlParentExaminesVariableUsedInDifferenceExpression() but includes them when it is called by controlParentExaminesVariableUsedInNonMappedNode() Special fix to handle the proper creation of for-statement initializers when there is an advanced match of for loops and the first clone fragment is using an additional variable declaration statement to initialize the for-statement initializer. This fix is for case 674-1-2 found in JFreeChart-1.0.10 (NiCad results) org.jfree.data.time.DynamicTimeSeriesCollection.appendData(float[]) org.jfree.data.time.DynamicTimeSeriesCollection.appendData(float[], int, int)
Relaxed precondition controlParentExaminesVariableInCondition() to include also variables being reported in differences.
Fixed Null Pointer Exception when calling ITypeBinding.getBound()

Improved the implementation of the precondition violation type added for the case where we have a number of mapped statements that is equal to zero. The mapped control predicate nodes having all statements nested inside them as unmapped nodes are no longer removed from the mapped statements, but they are simply examined in method computeRefactoringType()

Added a new precondition violation type for the case where we have a number of mapped statements that is equal to zero, after the post-processing phase that removes the mapped control predicate nodes having all statements nested inside them as unmapped nodes.
Avoiding pulling up already pulled up fields in the common or intermediate superclass.

Fixed the case where the variable to be returned by the extracted method belongs to the difference that should be parameterized and it is not a renamed variable. Added new precondition SWITCH_CASE_STATEMENT_WITHOUT_SWITCH to handle the case where at least one of the clone fragments contains a switch case statement, but does not contain the corresponding switch statement.
Added support for reporting the difference type SUBCLASS_TYPE_MISMATCH when a ParenthesizedExpression is compared with any expression that is not a NullLiteral.
In Extract Clone Refactoring, if at least one of the subclasses contains super method calls to a method to be pulled up in the intermediate superclass, then this method is not pulled up.
Handling properly clone fragments inside switch statements in precondition checkIfAllPossibleExecutionFlowsEndInReturn()

Reverting the replacement of getMaximumStates() with getMinimumDifferenceStates() Improved the implementation of precondition checkIfAllPossibleExecutionFlowsEndInReturn() to search for return statements only in the statements nested under the cloneStructureRoot instead of all statements of the PDG, when the statements under the cloneStructureRoot cover the entire block.

Improved the computation of the renamed variables by examining the mapped statements in ascending order and not allowing an already matched variable to be matched with another one. Improved the computation of weight for TYPE_COMPATIBLE_REPLACEMENT differences by adding in the weight the absolute value of the length difference of the corresponding binding signatures.
Undoing the update of ASTNodeMatcher to allow the matching of types "byte" and "int". Avoiding the rename of static fields that should be parameterized.
Replaced getMaximumStates() with getMinimumDifferenceStates()
Added support for reporting the difference type SUBCLASS_TYPE_MISMATCH when a CastExpression is compared with any expression that is not a NullLiteral.

Updated ASTNodeMatcher to allow the matching of types "byte" and "int". Improved Extract Clone Refactoring to rename the field accesses being parameterized in order to avoid variable identifier conflicts.
Finalized the rule for the Infeasible Refactoring precondition by examining whether all locally accessed methods in the clone fragments have matching signatures.
Fixed the computation of the return type for the extracted method.

Extended precondition checkIfAllPossibleExecutionFlowsEndInReturn() to include all return statements with expression. Relaxed the rule for the Infeasible Refactoring precondition by not allowing the common super interface implemented by the subclasses to be a tagging interface.
Minor fix in the detection of the commonly passed parameters.
Fixed another bug in the detection of the commonly passed parameters.
Fixed a bug in the detection of the commonly passed parameters.
Relaxed the computation of renamed variables to ignore the variables being used in differences for defined variables.

Fixed DivideAndConquerMatcher to handle properly the case when different types of control predicate statements are being matched. Fixed the computation of renamed variables to avoid the reporting of field access qualifiers.
The initializers of the fields being pulled up are checked for accessing types that should be imported.

If the common super type is an interface, and both subclasses implement it directly, then it is not added in the list of implemented interfaces of the intermediate superclass. If the common super type is an interface, and all its super-interfaces are tagging interfaces, then it is not added in the list of implemented interfaces of the intermediate superclass.
In PreconditionExaminer the mapped nodes nested under unmapped control predicates are moved to the unmapped nodes.
Added new Precondition Violation type for matched statements containing super method invocations. These statements cannot be extracted from the method in which they are called.

Improved the computation of the commonly passed parameters by examining the mapped statements in ascending order and not allowing an already matched parameter to be matched with another one. Updated methods containsMappedReturnStatementInDirectChildren() and containsMappedThrowStatementInDirectChildren() to also count unmapped return and throw statements, respectively, inside gaps.
Updated the detection of type-check elimination opportunities to support state variables having java.lang.String as type.

Extended Extract Clone Refactoring to introduce a default constructor in the intermediate superclass, if at least one of the subclasses declares all its constructors without super constructor calls and the other subclass does not contain a constructor calling a super constructor without parameters, and the common superclass declares a constructor without parameters.

Extended Extract Clone Refactoring to introduce a default constructor in the intermediate superclass, if at least one of the subclasses declares all its constructors without super constructor calls, and the common superclass declares a constructor without parameters.
Added new Precondition Violation type for matched statements being super constructor invocations. These statements cannot be extracted from the constructor in which they are called.

Added an intermediate level of mapping state comparison before the id-distance-based comparison in method findMaximumStateWithMinimumDifferences() The new comparison takes into account the number of non-distinct differences including type mismatches. This is a fix for case 123|3-8 found in JFreeChart-1.0.10 (NiCad results) org.jfree.chart.ChartFactory.createAreaChart org.jfree.chart.ChartFactory.createStackedBarChart
Fixed the value of the boolean symmetricalIfElse argument that should be passed to method processIfStatementChild()
This is a special fix for clone group 12|1-2 in project JFreeChart-1.0.10 (NiCad results) Unmapped statement left.closePath(); should be placed under "if (y0 >= 0.0)"

If both subclass implement a common interface, and the clone fragments contain a method call that passes as argument "this" reference, and the parameter type of the method call is the common interface type, then the intermediate superclass should implement this common interface. This is case 87|1-3 from NiCad results, and the method call causing the problem is subplot.removeChangeListener(this); org.jfree.chart.plot.CombinedRangeCategoryPlot.remove(CategoryPlot) org.jfree.chart.plot.CombinedDomainCategoryPlot.remove(CategoryPlot)

Removed an unnecessary if check in DivideAndConquerMatcher Method getCommonPassedParameters() is PreconditionExaminer checks if the declarations of the variables have been found in order to add an entry to the returned map.

In PreconditionExaminer the mapped nodes nested under unmapped try blocks are moved to the unmapped nodes. Fields passedParametersG1 and passedParametersG2 in PreconditionExaminer have been removed, since they are no longer used.
Method instantiatesLocalVariable() excludes the instantiation of array variables.
Extended the reporting of difference type SUBCLASS_TYPE_MISMATCH when different expression types are being compared.
When two ClassInstanceCreation expressions are matched, their arguments, expression, and anonymous class declaration should be compared only if the class type is exactly matched.
Added method match(InstanceofExpression node, Object other) in ASTNodeMatcher.

Improved the mapping of statements based on code fragment decomposition. The comparison of mapping states based on the Id difference of the mapped statements is now relative to the Ids of the first mapped statements.

Excluded the reporting of difference type SUBCLASS_TYPE_MISMATCH when a SimpleName is compared with a NullLiteral. In the introduction of parameters for the differences, when the type of one expression is primitive and the type of the other expression is null, the type of the parameter being introduced is the corresponding wrapper class type for the primitive type.
Added support for reporting the difference type SUBCLASS_TYPE_MISMATCH when a ClassInstanceCreation is compared with a SimpleName and vice versa.
TypeBinding.isEqualTo() is unreliable. Added a comparison of the qualified names of the type bindings, wherever isEqualTo() is used.
Extended ASTNodeMatcher to ignore non-parameterizable differences found in expressions nested under catch clauses, finally blocks, and anonymous class declarations.

Extended ASTNodeMatcher to reduce the weight of TYPE_COMPATIBLE_REPLACEMENT differences that are reversed from previous differences appearing in the arguments of method calls and class instance creations.
The difference type TYPE_COMPATIBLE_REPLACEMENT is reported with a weight equal to the size of bending signatures corresponding to the difference.
Fixed Null Pointer Exception in method instantiatesLocalVariable()
Fixed again the comparison of a static method invocation with a non-static method invocation.
Fixed method instantiatesLocalVariable() in PDGNode. The instantiated type could be a subclass of the defined local variable type.
Fixed java.lang.ClassCastException: org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.AnonymousClassDeclaration cannot be cast to org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.TypeDeclaration
Fixed DivideAndConquerMatcher to avoid the matching of 'if/else-if' structures with a different number of clauses. Fixed method insertCDTNodeInTree() to insert properly 'else' nodes in the CDT tree.
Fixed the comparison of a static method invocation with a non-static method invocation.

Improved method isParameterizable() to avoid the matching of method calls with all of the following differences: 1) missing invocation expression 2) different method name 3) different number of arguments or same number of type compatible arguments
Improved the matching of Parenthesized expressions.
Improved precondition checkIfAllPossibleExecutionFlowsEndInReturn()
Handled the case where the clone fragments belong to methods declared inside anonymous class declarations.
TypeBinding.isEqualTo() is unreliable. Added a comparison of the qualified names of the type bindings, wherever isEqualTo() is used in ASTNodeMatcher.

This is a special fix for clone group 263|1-3 in project JFreeChart-1.0.10 (Deckard results) Unmapped statement left.clone(); should be placed under the "else" mapping that has "if (y0 >= 0.0)" as its symmetrical if node pair.

This is a special fix for clone group 18506 in project JFreeChart-1.0.10 (CCFinder results) org.jfree.chart.labels.BubbleXYItemLabelGenerator.createItemArray() org.jfree.chart.labels.StandardXYZToolTipGenerator.createItemArray() regarding the mapping of statements Number z = dataset.getZ(series, item); -> Number x = dataset.getX(series, item); that should be moved at the beginning of the extracted method.

This is a special fix for clone group 8996 in project JFreeChart-1.0.10 (CCFinder results) org.jfree.experimental.chart.swt.demo.SWTBarChartDemo1.main org.jfree.experimental.chart.swt.demo.SWTPieChartDemo1.main to allow the analysis of static methods with similar signatures, but different implementations, being called by the clone fragments. In such a case, a new difference is introduced between the clone fragments, so that the static method calls will be parameterized, since it is not possible to move the static methods along with the extracted code (i.e., the static methods being called are not clones).

Broke down clone refactoring type PULL_UP_TO_NEW_SUPERCLASS to 5 sub-categories: PULL_UP_TO_NEW_INTERMEDIATE_SUPERCLASS_EXTENDING_COMMON_INTERNAL_SUPERCLASS PULL_UP_TO_NEW_INTERMEDIATE_SUPERCLASS_IMPLEMENTING_COMMON_INTERNAL_INTERFACE PULL_UP_TO_NEW_SUPERCLASS_EXTENDING_COMMON_EXTERNAL_SUPERCLASS PULL_UP_TO_NEW_SUPERCLASS_IMPLEMENTING_COMMON_EXTERNAL_INTERFACE PULL_UP_TO_NEW_SUPERCLASS_EXTENDING_OBJECT
Improved the collection of thrown exceptions in PDG nodes.

Added the logic for extracting the type from a variable declaration to RefactoringUtility. Fixed the case where a qualified type must be introduced to a parameter of the extracted method due to type ambiguity.

A variable passed as parameter to the extracted method is initialized with a default value when all following conditions hold: 1) the declaration of the variable has no initializer and it is a variable declaration fragment 2) the variable is not a parameter of the original method 3) the variable is not a field 4) the variable is declared outside the clone fragment, while it is modified inside the clone fragment
Added method getDescendants() in ControlDependenceTreeNode
Added support for reporting the difference type SUBCLASS_TYPE_MISMATCH when a QualifiedName is compared with a SimpleName and vice versa.
Updated PDG to avoid having fields referencing VariableDeclaration (ASTNode) objects. Added support for generating qualified types for type bindings.
Fixed the proper addition of the required import statements, when a constructor should be copied in one of the subclasses.
Improved the initialization of the variables passed as parameters to the extracted method with a default value, if they are not already initialized.
Fixed the computation of the return type binding of the extracted method in the case where the clone fragments have multiple return statements returning different types.
Improved the generation of a member type (i.e., a type nested inside another type) from its type binding.

Minor fix to method findMethodsCalledFromType() to consider the direct superclass of the type corresponding to a SUBCLASS_TYPE_MISMATCH difference, as a potential type in which the examined method calls and field accesses could be declared.
Fixed the refactoring of symmetrical if-else-if statements.
Extended method cloneFragmentsDoNotAccessFieldsOrMethods() to check also if 'this' expressions are accessed in the clone fragments.

Reimplemented the method checking the need for adding a return statement at the end of the extracted method. Only the last if-else-if chain is required to contain a return or throw statement in every clause.

Extended the method checking the need for adding a return statement at the end of the extracted method, by relaxing the requirement for all if statements to have a final else clause to only the last if statement in the clone fragments.
Extended Extract Clone Refactoring to initialize with a default value the variables passed as parameters to the extracted method, if they are not already initialized.

Removed condition MethodCallAnalyzer.equalSignatureIgnoringSubclassTypeDifferences(methodDeclaration1.resolveBinding(), methodDeclaration2.resolveBinding()) examined for methods or method signatures to be pulled up. Case 8996 should be fixed in a different way org.jfree.experimental.chart.swt.demo.SWTBarChartDemo1.main() org.jfree.experimental.chart.swt.demo.SWTPieChartDemo1.main()

Improved the creation of constructors in the intermediate superclass based on the common super-constructors called in the constructors of the subclasses. Updated method superclassInheritedOnlyByRefactoredSubclasses() to check if the subclasses to be refactored are extended by other subclasses.
When extracting a Utility Class, the calls of static methods in the clone fragments, which do not correspond to duplicated method declarations, are parameterized.

Fixed the handling of qualified names where the difference is on the qualifiers. This problem was introduced after extending method getParentExpressionOfMethodNameOrTypeName() to return the parent expression in case of field accesses.

Improved method infeasibleRefactoring() to include clone fragments with a common super type that is a class, and at least one of the subclasses does not have the common super type as a direct superclass.
Improved method allConditionalMappedChildrenContainReturnStatement() to take into account whether if statements have a final else clause.
Avoided adding a return statement with a default value at the end of the extracted method, if all conditional statements contain a return statement.

Added a return statement with a default value at the end of the extracted method, if there are no return statements directly nested under the extracted method. Added special handling for type java.lang.Class in the parameters passed to the extracted method.
Included fields in the computation of commonly passed parameters.
Fixed the code finding the commonly passed parameters to consider as common parameters also those variables having different types extending a common superclass or interface.
Updated ThrownExceptionVisitor to return also the exception types thrown in Throw statements.
Added support for reporting the difference type SUBCLASS_TYPE_MISMATCH when a FieldAccess is compared with a SimpleName and vice versa.
Created method getRenamedVariableBindings() to recover the pairs of variable bindings for the variables found as renamed between the clone fragments.
Extended method getParentExpressionOfMethodNameOrTypeName() to return the parent ClassInstanceCreation from a QualifiedName representing a Type.
Added a check examining whether the common superclass already contains a method declaration having the same signature with methods to be pulled up from the subclasses.
The commonly implemented interfaces by the subclasses are no longer copied to the intermediate superclass.
Added a check to avoid processing the same super constructor calls declared in different constructors of the subclasses.
Fixed method addImportDeclaration() used for adding manually import declarations to a compilation unit.
Fixed the computation of the parameter types introduced for differences.
The constructors added to the intermediate superclass are matched based on the arguments of the super constructor call inside them (not based on the constructor arguments).

Added back the feature for copying missing constructors in the subclasses, but in the current implementation it is checked whether the subclasses already contain a constructor with the same signature.

Extended PreconditionExaminer to store the fields being directly/indirectly modified in the clone fragments. Removed the feature for copying missing constructors in the subclasses. The constructors added to the intermediate superclass should be created based on the arguments of the super constructor call inside them (not based on the constructor arguments). The fields modified in the clone fragments are pulled up to the superclass, even if the subclasses implement the Serializable interface. In the future, we should consider creating abstract setter/getter methods in the common superclass for the modified fields that need to be serialized.
Fixed method parameterIsUsedByNodesWithoutDifferences() to handle properly renamed variables.
Avoided pulling up methods declared in the common superclass. The fields accessed through getter methods are considered only as indirectly accessed fields.
Fixed method infeasibleRefactoring() to return true if at least one of the subclasses does not have java.lang.Object as a superclass.
Fixed the case where the clone fragment is a statement directly nested under an if or an else clause.

Moved the logic for finding the Clone refactoring that should be applied to class PreconditionExaminer. Added a new precondition violation that considers the refactoring infeasible, if the common super type is an interface and the classes where the clones belong to extend a superclass other than java.lang.Object
Fixed commonSuperType to return java.lang.Object in the case where one of the input classes extends only java.lang.Object and does not implement any interface.

The primitive types representing numbers (byte, double, float, int, long, and short) are considered as matching types with java.lang.Number The common superclass of a primitive type representing a number and java.lang.Number is java.lang.Number
Improved the computation of common superclass by giving preference to inheritance hierarchy leaves being classes.
Fixed commonSuperType to return java.lang.Object in the case where the input classes extend only java.lang.Object and do not implement any interface.

The difference type SUBCLASS_TYPE_MISMATCH is reported for FieldAccess and SuperFieldAccess AST nodes. Added support for parameterizing commonly accessed fields having different types. Fixed the extraction of types from the expressions of catch clauses.
Updated TryStatementObject so that the exceptions declared in catch blocks are considered as being declared in the try statement expressions.
Added support to have differences with weights. In ARGUMENT_NUMBER_MISMATCH difference type, the weight is set equal to the product of the number of arguments.

Improved Extract Clone Refactoring to replace super method calls with regular method calls, when the clone fragment is pulled up to the common super class declaring the methods corresponding to the super calls. Improved the detection of the common superclass by creating inheritance hierarchies from the initially extracted common super type bindings, and returning the type binding found in the deepest level of the inheritance hierarchies.

Improved the precondition about examining whether the arguments (having a different type) passed in method/constructor calls, have a common superclass type that can be still passed as a valid argument type.
Fixed a bug in determining whether a local variable is declared inside a method of an anonymous class.
Improved method match(MethodInvocation, Object) to avoid the matching of static with non-static method calls.
Fixed a NullPointerException in the previous fix.

Added thrown exception types by Method objects in the CompilationUnit Cache. MethodCallAnalyzer stores and retrieves thrown exception types in/from the CompilationUnitCache. Fixed method processIdenticalPDGNodes() in DivideAndConquerMatcher to avoid the processing of new mappings for already mapped nodes.
The precondition violation EXPRESSION_DIFFERENCE_IS_VOID_METHOD_CALL has been extended to expression differences that are non-void method calls, but cover the entire statement.
Replaced ITypeBinding.isEqualTo() with ITypeBinding.getQualifiedName().equals()
Fixed Extract Clone Refactoring to introduce an intermediate superclass in the case the common superType of the classes containing the clone fragments is an interface.

Added a new precondition violation to examine whether the arguments (having a different type) passed in method/constructor calls, have a common superclass type that can be still passed as a valid argument type.
Improved support for adding missing constructors in the subclasses when the clone is pulled up in an intermediate superclass. Constructors existing only in the second subclass are properly handled.
Added method addTypeBinding() in class ExtractCloneRefactoring to deal with typeBindings being equal based on IBinding.isEqualTo() but not Object.equals()
Added support for adding missing constructors in the subclasses when the clone is pulled up in an intermediate superclass.

A constructor in the intermediate superclass is created even if the subclass constructors have different super constructor calls (in terms of AST similarity), as long as the super constructor calls have the same argument types.
The parent node of a statement is not always a Block. It could also be a SwitchStatement. This bug created a ClassCastException in Extract Clone and Extract Method refactorings.

The precondition that examines whether a class member accessed through different subclass references is declared in the common superclass has been extended to direct field accesses. (previously only method calls were examined)

Fixed the parameterization of field accesses which are used as expressions in conditional statements (if, while). Improved the comparison of TypeLiteral nodes in ASTNodeMatcher. Fixed the extraction of the type from a VariableDeclaration to take into account the different ways an array type can be declared. For example, PeriodAxisLabelInfo info[] = new PeriodAxisLabelInfo[1]; PeriodAxisLabelInfo[] info = new PeriodAxisLabelInfo[2]; Introduced class RefactoringUtility, which contains functionality used commonly by all Refactoring implementations.
Improved the computation of the returned variables by taking into account the output dependencies only if the variable is declared in one of the mapped statements.
Output dependencies are also taken into account in the computation of the returned variables.
Bug fix for the case where the classes of the inheritance hierarchy belong to the same CompilationUnit with the code performing the Runtime Type Identification.
Initialized fields variablesToBeReturnedG1 and variablesToBeReturnedG2

The precondition that examines whether a method called through different subclass references is declared in the common superclass has been extended to method calls with signatures having parameter/return types being subclass types of a common superclass type. (previously only method calls with exactly the same signature were examined)

In some cases isEqualTo() returns true for type bindings corresponding to different type declarations. A typical example is classes org.jfree.chart.labels.BubbleXYItemLabelGenerator and org.jfree.chart.labels.StandardXYZToolTipGenerator in project JFreeChart-1.0.10.

Output dependencies are also taken into account in the computation of common passed parameters. This is a fix for the following case: org.jfree.chart.plot.dial.junit	DialCapTests	testSerialization	()V	188	199 org.jfree.chart.plot.dial.junit	DialCapTests	testSerialization	()V	213	224

The renamed local variables used within the clone fragments are properly passed as parameters to the extracted method. Fixed a bug that skipped the addition of node gaps, if the gapped node was nested under a try block, which was not part of the clone fragment.

Fixed a bug in Extract Clone Refactoring related to the variable being returned by the extracted method. Improved the computation of the exception types thrown by the statements in the clone fragments.

If one of the additionally pulled up methods is static, then the method created in the superclass should be static. Improved the computation of the exception types that should be thrown in the signature of the extracted method.

-In some cases isEqualTo() returns true for type bindings corresponding to different type declarations. A typical example is classes org.jfree.chart.plot.CombinedDomainXYPlot and org.jfree.chart.plot.CombinedRangeXYPlot in project JFreeChart-1.0.10. This issue is fixed by comparing the qualified names of the type bindings. -In Extract Clone Refactoring the commonly implemented interfaces in the subclasses are copied to the intermediate superclass. -In Extract Clone Refactoring the additional clone methods being pulled up in the common superclass are examined whether their modifier or return type should be updated. -In Extract Clone Refactoring method cloneFragmentsDoNotAccessFieldsOrMethods() tolerates non-static method calls in only one of the clone fragments. This feature needs to be improved to check if the non-static method calls correspond to static method calls in the other clone fragment.

Extracted static method isTaggingInterface() in class ASTNodeMatcher. Extract Clone Refactoring introduces a Utility class for clones belonging to classes having a tagging interface as the common superclass.

Improved PreconditionExaminer to detect renamed fields in addition to renamed variables. Differences corresponding to renamed fields should be parameterized, but should not be checked for precondition violations.

Improved the computation of the fields accessed within the clone fragments by excluding the fields accessed in the clone differences. ASTNodeMatcher has been extended to compare the types of QualifiedName nodes.

-In DivideAndConquerMatcher, the statements before the clone fragments at level 0 are excluded from being matched, if the fullTreeMatch option is set to false (previously only the statements after the clone fragments were excluded from being matched). -The unmatched CDT nodes are inserted under the matched CDT nodes. -The precondition controlParentExaminesVariableInCondition() is extended to examine all variables that appear in the conditional expression of a parent control statement (previously only the left hand-side operands of infix and instance-of expressions were considered).
Avoided pulling up fields that are not declared in the subclasses.
Fixed overridesMethod() to exclude the private methods declared in a superclass from being examined if they are overridden.
The files containing the clones must be opened in the editor before refactoring.
Fixed the update of access modifiers when an abstract method is introduced in the superclass for private methods in the subclasses.
Added fields that are defined by methods called inside the clones in the list of fields to be pulled up.
Excluded interface java.lang.Cloneable from the list of accepted common super types.

Added import declarations for the thrown exception types in the signatures of the methods containing the clones. Added support to copy the constructors containing a superConstructorInvocation from the subclasses to the intermediate superclass.
Improved the computation of the required import declarations for the extracted clone.
Extracted the precondition examination logic from the SubTreeMapper subclasses to class PreconditionExaminer. DivideAndConquerMatcher delegates to PreconditionExaminer.
Fixed the refactoring of an if/else matched with a ternary operator.
Excluded interfaces Serializable, Runnable, and Comparable from the list of accepted common super types. Improved the matching of variable declaration statements with assignment statements.
A control dependence node is created only for the conditional expressions that are direct children of expression statements. Fixed a bug in method getAllSuperTypesUpToCommonSuperclass()
Extended method commonSuperType() in class ASTNodeMatcher to find also the common superInterface of two types (if there is no common superclass).
Fixed a bug in computeSlice
Fixed a NullPointerException in method compareTypes of class ConditionalLoopASTNodeMatcher.

Improved precondition for the parameterization of differences isParameterizableExpression() to ignore incoming dependencies from advanced matched nodes. Updated ASTNodeMatcher to report only differences in the types of the data structure expressions of the advanced matched loops.
Added String.charAt(int) in the list of method bindings used for accessing an element of a data structure.
Updated the rank URL
Added Properies.propertyNames() in the list of method bindings instantiating an enumeration.
Fixed NullPointerException in method getOccurrencesOfSimpleName()
Encapsulated the addition of differences in ASTNodeMatcher to check for duplicated differences. Fixed the detection of unmapped in the SubTreeMapper classes.

Updated ExtractCloneRefactoring to parameterize differences in additionally matched statements. Updated ASTNodeMatcher to report differences in the data structure accesses within the bodies of the advanced matched loops.

Fixed precondition for the parameterization of differences isParameterizableExpression() to ignore incoming dependencies from advanced matched nodes. Updated ASTNodeMatcher to report differences in the data structure expressions of the advanced matched loops.

Fixed the mapping of the following case in Apache Ant 1.7.0 /apache-ant-1.7.0/src/org/apache/tools/ant/taskdefs/optional/dotnet/WsdlToDotnet.java
void applyExtraArgs(NetCommand)
/apache-ant-1.7.0/src/org/apache/tools/ant/taskdefs/optional/dotnet/DotnetBaseMatchingTask.java
void addFilesToCommand(Hashtable, NetCommand)
Added support for obtaining the additionally matched fragments at the TreeNodeMatchPair and SubTreeMatch level.
Fixed the detection of the control variable in complex infix expressions.
Improved the refactoring of advanced loop clones by ignoring the differences in their conditional expressions.
Fixed the matching of parameterized and wildcard type bindings

-Improved ASTNodeMatcher by tolerating the presence of Variable Type mismatches along with Method Invocation Name mismatches. This fixes the mapping solution for the following case in project EMF-2.4.1 org.eclipse.emf.ecore.xml.type.internal.RegEx.RegularExpression.matchString(Context, Op, int, int, int) org.eclipse.emf.ecore.xml.type.internal.RegEx.RegularExpression.matchCharacterIterator(Context, Op, int, int, int) -Updated plug-in version to 5.0.24
Updated plug-in version to 5.0.23
Fixed a bug related to the handling of Synchronized blocks during the generation of the PDG.

Fixed Extract Class Refactoring to make the extracted class implement the Serializable interface, if the source class implements the Serializable interface and at least one extracted field is non-transient.
Added support for checking whether a method with the same name already exists in a class when performing an Extract Method Refactoring.

Fixed the extraction of thrown exceptions in PDGNodes. Class Instance Creations throwing exceptions are also taken into account in addition to method invocations. Thanks to Rodrigo Morales (cole Polytechnique de Montral) for reporting this problem.
Moved the matching of expressions outside the for loop.
Expanded the list of methods returning the size or length of collections.

The updating of the model is no longer performed asynchronously. This bug caused model inconsistencies when detecting refactoring opportunities in the new code elements introduced by a previously applied refactoring.
Made the Slice Profile dialog resizable. Added vertical scrolling to the Slice Profile table.
Added getSignature() to interface AbstractMethodDeclaration
Moved getSignature() to ConstructorObject and added a delegate method to MethodObject
Fixed the refactoring of clones already containing parameters with argN names (where N is an integer starting from 0)

Fixed the Extract Method Refactoring mechanics when the variable criterion declaration statement is nested deeper than the extracted method invocation insertion statement. This fix improves the extraction of variable anchorRect (at block B8) from method drawDomainMarker() in class AbstractXYItemRenderer of project JFreeChart 1.0.14.
Fixed a NullPointerException when resolving the TypeBinding of NullLiteral expressions.
Extended the collection of comments for anonymous class declarations.
Added support for collecting comments (i.e., line, block, and javadoc comments) at TypeDeclaration, MethodDeclaration and FieldDeclaration level.

-In the precondition examining the unification of variables having different subclass types, we consider that the methods declared in the common superclass include the methods declared in the classes/interfaces inherited/implemented by the common superclass. -This fix supports cases of Feature Envy, where a method accesses entities from a superclass type through a subclass type reference. If the access map contains entities being accessed from a subclass and a superclass type, then the entities being accessed from the superclass type are added to the entities being accessed from the subclass type.

Updated the slice-profile view to display all local variables declared inside the body of the examined method. Added an option that enables only the variables with a scope covering the entire method body.
Fixed the refactoring of clones with additionally matched statements coming from the advanced matching of control predicate statements.

Fixed a bug in Extract Clone Refactoring. If an additional clone method to be pulled up (called from the main clone methods) accesses fields that participate in serialization, then an abstract method with its signature is added in the superclass.

- Excluded the cases where a setter method call is replaced with field assignment from the VOID_RETURN_TYPE precondition. - Fixed a NullPinterException in method getAdditionalFragments() of class ConditionalLoop - Updated plug-in version to 5.0.18
Added java.lang.Iterable as the superInterface of Collection types.
Fixed the matching of default switch cases.

Added support for the advanced matching of a VariableDeclaration statement having an initializer with a VariableDeclaration statement not having an initializer + an Assignment statement initializing the declared variable.

- The variables declared in additionally matched statements are also taken into account in the detection of renamed variables. - Updated plug-in version to 5.0.17 git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant/CloneRefactoring@732 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

- modified ASTNodeMatcher.loopMatch(AbstractLoop, Object) so, if one node is a ConditionalLoop and the other is an EnhancedForLoop, the initialization of a new variable in the ConditionalLoop body matching the formal parameter of the EnhancedForLoop (if there is one that matches) will be added to the additionallyMatchedFragments - modified TernaryControlStructure.match(TernaryControlStructure, ASTNodeMatcher) to always return false (because of the design of ASTNodeMatcher.match(ExpressionStatement, Object) this ternary match will never be reached. It is kept because it is an abstract method in AbstractControlStructure needed for polymorphism - added dataStructureAccessMethods field to specify all the methods that can be used to initialize a new variable in a ConditionalLoop using it's control variable's data structure - added all logic for finding the initialization of a new variable in the ConditionalLoop in AbstractLoopUtilities - added support for field access when finding the dataStructureExpression of a ControlVariable in ControlVariable.getEndValue(SimpleName, ASTNode) git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant/CloneRefactoring@731 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Added a new precondition regarding unmapped statements and incoming control dependences from parent 'if' statements. If an unmapped statement is using a variable, and this variable is examined in the conditional expression of a matched parent 'if' statement (that will be extracted), then the unmapped statement cannot be moved outside this 'if' statement. A variable is considered to be examined, if it is used inside the left operand of an infix or instanceof expression. Examples of variable examinations found in cases 441-1-2, 319-1-3, 326-1-2 in JFreeChart-1.0.10 (Deckard results): if (count > 1) if (count % 2 == 1) if (ds != null) if (this.minute != FIRST_MINUTE_IN_HOUR) git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant/CloneRefactoring@695 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

This is a fix for case 360-3-6 found in JFreeChart-1.0.10 (Deckard results)

1) The variables inside expressions belonging to differences are excluded from the analysis of renamed variables. 2) The method calls inside expressions belonging to differences are not analyzed to get locally accessed fields and called methods. 3) Fields accessed in methods called within the clone fragments are pulled up only if the corresponding methods that access the fields are Type-1 clones and also pulled up in the common superclass. 4) If the subclasses containing the clone fragments are not direct subclasses of the common superclass and the clone fragment is extracted to the common superclass, then called methods having identical signatures in the subclasses are not introduced as abstract methods in the common superclass, but as concrete methods with a default return type. This solution is applied to avoid having to provide an implementation for the introduced abstract method in the remaining subclasses. Clone group 173, JFreeChart 1.0.10 (Deckard results)

Introduced a new decomposition in the mapping problem by grouping identical statements. The following cases in JFreeChart 1.0.10 are matched faster now: (Group 64, Pair 1-2): org.jfree.chart.annotations.junit.CategoryPointerAnnotationTests#testEquals and org.jfree.chart.annotations.junit.XYPointerAnnotationTests#testEquals (Group 108, Pair 1-2): org.jfree.chart.labels.junit.StandardXYItemLabelGeneratorTests#testEquals and org.jfree.chart.labels.junit.StandardXYToolTipGeneratorTests#testEquals (Group 176, Pair 1-2): org.jfree.chart.plot.dial.junit.DialCapTests#testEquals and org.jfree.chart.plot.dial.junit.StandardDialFrameTests#testEquals (Group 213, Pair 1-2): org.jfree.chart.axis.junit.DateAxisTests#testEquals and org.jfree.chart.axis.junit.NumberAxisTests#testEquals (Group 247, Pair 3-6): org.jfree.chart.renderer.xy.junit.XYAreaRenderer2Tests#testDrawWithNullInfo and org.jfree.chart.renderer.xy.junit.XYStepRendererTests#testDrawWithNullInfo Fixed three problems in Extract Clone refactoring.
1) If the classes containing the clone fragments are not direct subclasses of their common superclass,
the common code is placed in the common superclass instead of an intermediate class.
2) Import declarations are added for the types used in the signatures of the methods being pulled up.
3) In the computation of commonly passed parameters from the two clone fragments, sometimes the data dependencies for the same variables appear in a different order.

Removed condition "nodeId >= mappedNodes.first().getId() && nodeId <= mappedNodes.last().getId()" in the examination of precondition violations for unmapped statements. In the case org.eclipse.emf.ecore.xml.type.internal.RegEx.matchesIgnoreCase
the first statement inside the do-while loop was unmatched.
However, its examination was skipped because of the aforementioned condition.
The do-while loop gets the ID following after the ID of the last statement inside its body.

are also examined for precondition violations.

Introduced major changes: 1) ASTNodeMatcher handles InfixExpressions being children of MethodInvocation, SuperMethodInvocation, ClassInstanceCreation, ArrayCreation, ArrayAccess, and Assignment expressions. 2) The total number of differences is replaced with the total distinct number of differences in the determination of minimum differences. 3) A new strategy is applied for level-0 nodes. A tree of CloneStructureNode objects is used to represent the control structure of the clone. Each node in the tree contains a node mapping (except for the root). The extracted method will be generated by traversing the clone structure tree starting from the root. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant/CloneRefactoring@465 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The extracted method invocation is placed (1) as the initializer of a variable declaration statement, if the extracted method computes a variable that is used in the remaining statements of the original method. (2) as the expression of a return statement, if the extracted code contains return statements (with expressions). (3) as the expression of an expression statement, if the extracted code does not contain return statements. The PDGNodeMapping objects have a new boolean attribute indicating whether the mapping corresponds to symmetrical if statements.

Fixed the problem of inherited static fields being accessed by a method to be moved. After the move the inherited static fields should be statically accessed using the name of the class in which they are declared. This bug affects both the Extract Class and Move Method refactorings. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@394 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

- Added new precondition for Move Method refactoring. The variable (parameter or field of target class type) through which the moved method will be invoked must not be assigned within the body of the candidate method to be moved. The reason is that the variable should be replaced with "this" expression in the moved method and "this" expression cannot be assigned with a value. - In Replace Conditional with Polymorphism refactoring, the context class must be public
when the type-checking branches access fields/methods of the context class
and the subclasses belong to a different package with respect to the context class.

The try/catch blocks and throw statements are handled according to the approach proposed by Allen & Horwitz (2003). M. Allen, and S. Horwitz, "Slicing Java Programs that Throw and Catch Exceptions",
ACM SIGPLAN Workshop on Partial Evaluation and semantics-based Program Manipulation, pp. 44-54, 2003.

git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@377 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Added a rule for the preservation of output dependences. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@376 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The unlabeled break and continue statements within the body of loops and the break statements within the body of switch statements are handled according to the augmented program dependence graph (APDG) approach proposed by Ball & Horwitz (1993), Kumar & Horwitz (2002). T. Ball, and S. Horwitz, "Slicing Programs with Arbitrary Control Flow",
First International Workshop on Automated and Algorithmic Debugging, pp. 206-222, 1993.

S. Kumar, and S. Horwitz, "Better Slicing of Programs with Jumps and Switches",
Fifth International Conference on Fundamental Approaches to Software Engineering, pp. 96- 112, 2002.

Fixed bug in refactoring application. The following line:

array[0] = value; (assignment of a specific item of an array. The array is an extracted field.)

was changed by this:

newClass.setArray(value); (as an assignment the line is replaced with a setter.)

Now it is changed by this:

newClass.getArray()[0] = value; (the assignment remains and the item of the array is accessed by a getter.)

Improved the implementation of method processExternalMethodInvocation in PDGNode in order to be able to handle super method invocations. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@356 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The node criteria of the additionally included object slices are examined whether they exist inside the corresponding block-based region. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@355 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
additional code to revision 353 git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@354 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

-Improved the speed of slice computation when constructing unions of slices. -The complete computation and object state slices have been extended to include the object state slice of any object reference which is used in the initial slice. -The slice profile of a method is composed from the complete computation and object state slices of the local variables whose scope is the block corresponding to the method body. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@353 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
