Method processArgumentsOfInternalMethodInvocation is invoked only by PDGStatementNode and PDGControlPredicateNode (PDGNode subclasses). git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@351 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Ignore fields whose declaring class has no qualified name, such as fields which are declared in anonymous classes. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@350 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Removed an unused parameter from method handleAlreadyAnalyzedExternalMethod. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@349 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Indexing is performed for the subclasses of the types belonging to the project under examination. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@348 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The case where an argument is passed as parameter to an abstract invoked method is properly analyzed. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@347 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The slice profile of a method includes only the local variables whose scope is the block corresponding to the method body. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@346 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

An additional slice extraction threshold value has been added which is related with the maximum depth of method call graph traversal for libraries. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@345 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The variables which are not defined within the body of the examined method are automatically excluded from its slice profile. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@344 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Added a calculator for slice-based cohesion metrics. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@343 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

An additional slice extraction threshold value has been added which is related with the size of the methods being examined. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@342 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The fields which are defined through this reference are now properly handled regarding statement duplication. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@341 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Improved the code related with internal program analysis. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@340 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Improved the code for the handling of external method invocations. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@339 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
In the application of Move Method refactoring, the javadoc @param tags are properly updated. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@338 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Added two Annotation markers in order to highlight slice statements that will be duplicated in red color and slice statements that will be removed from the original method in green color. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@337 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: The prefix expressions having a field as operand and +, -, !, ~ as operator are properly handled. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@336 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Pulled up duplicated code existing in Replace Type Code with State/Strategy and Replace Conditional with Polymorphism refactorings to a common abstract superclass named PolymorphismRefactoring. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@335 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

In the application of Replace Type Code with State/Strategy and Replace Conditional with Polymorphism refactorings, the required import declarations are now added using class ImportRewrite. Moreover, the changes to already existing classes are represented with CompilationUnitChange objects. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@334 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

-Move Method Refactoring preconditions have been updated: A candidate target class should not be selected as final target class if there exists another candidate target class that inherits it. This means that the method to be moved accesses members from classes having an inheritance relationship and thus can only be moved to the subclass in order to continue having access to the inherited members. -Move Method Refactoring mechanics have been updated:
The invocations of static methods inside the body of the moved method
which are inherited from a superclass of the source class,
are replaced with static invocations through source class name
after the move to target class.


git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@333 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The resulting slice extraction refactoring opportunities are grouped based on common variables used as slicing criteria and sorted in ascending order according to their average duplication ratio. In the case where two or more slice groups have an average duplication ratio equal to zero, they are sorted in descending order according to the maximum number of extracted statements of the slices belonging to each group. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@332 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
additional code to revision 330 git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@331 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Move Method Refactoring preconditions have been updated: The method to be moved should not contain any super field accesses. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@330 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

In the application of Move Method refactoring, the original method should be turned into a method that delegates to the moved one, in the case where a subclass invokes the method to be moved by means of a super method invocation. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@329 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

In the application of Move Method refactoring the required import declarations to target class are added using class ImportRewrite. Moreover, the changes to source and target class are represented with CompilationUnitChange objects. Finally, TypeVisitor collects all SimpleTypes being declared within the method to be moved. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@328 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Fixed a problem in the application of Move Method refactoring that appeared when the method to be moved accessed through a reference to the target class a field belonging to the superclass of the target class. In this case the reference from which the superclass field was accessed was not removed from the body of the moved method. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@327 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Fixed a bug in the the application of Extract Method refactoring which is related with the way that the name of the extracted method was obtained. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@326 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

AST information for analyzed library classes is no longer permanently stored in memory. All references to MethodDeclarations and VariableDeclarations have been replaced with references to the keys of their bindings. A separate cache mechanism is employed that keeps a constant number of CompilationUnits corresponding to library IClassFiles in a queue. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@325 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Moved field className from class MethodObject to class ConstructorObject. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@324 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Added support to compare the signature of a constructor declaration with a class instance creation. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@323 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

-The indispensable statements are also examined in order to decide whether the slice of a break or continue statement will be duplicated. -An anti-dependence exists between statement A and B due to variable x if there is a flow path starting from statement A that uses x and ending to statement B that defines x, regardless of intermediate statements that may use variable x. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@322 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Break and continue statements inside loops are properly handled. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@321 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

An additional rule has been added regarding slice extraction: If a return statement is directly or indirectly control dependent on a statement belonging to a given slice, then this slice is rejected from being suggested as a refactoring opportunity. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@320 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The size of the CompilationUnit cache can be set by the user in the Preference Page of JDeodorant. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@319 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Try/catch blocks are properly copied to the extracted method and removed from the original method if necessary. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@318 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The rule regarding the duplication of all node criteria for an object slice union has been programmed with an alternative way. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@317 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

When the identification of code smells is performed on the same project, then only the compilation units that have been changed or added are parsed again. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@316 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Fixed the handling of blocks that exist within the body of a switch statement in the construction of control flow graph. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@315 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

-The identification of Feature Envy and Type Checking code smells can now be performed on a whole Java Project, a specific Package of a project, a specific Compilation Unit and a specific Type (along with its nested types) by selecting the appropriate element on the Package Explorer. -A Progress Monitor has been added for the AST parsing of the selected Java Project. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@314 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The analysis of external method invocations also includes the methods which are invoked through parameters that ate passed as arguments in method invocations inside the body of the method under examination. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@313 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

In a polymorphic method call the concrete implementations of the invoked abstract method may reside to subclasses existing in an inheritance depth level which is deeper than first level. This issue has been extended also to internal method invocations, including interface methods. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@312 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The computation of indispensable nodes and passed parameters for the union of static slices has been improved. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@311 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The analysis of external method invocations also included the methods which are invoked through field references. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@310 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

In a polymorphic method call the concrete implementations of the invoked abstract method may reside to subclasses existing in an inheritance depth level which is deeper than first level.As a result, method getSubTypes() of class LibraryClassStorage returns also the subtypes at any depth level whose superclass is an abstract type. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@309 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

-Fixed the handling of empty loops in the construction of control flow graphs -Alias Analysis can be enabled/disabled in the Preference Page of the tool git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@308 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

-The results of the identification process can be saved in a tab delimited text file by clicking on "Save Results" button. -Increased CompilationUnit cache capacity from 5 to 10. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@307 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The CompilationUnit caching mechanism has been enhanced to enable the locking of a specific CompilationUnit. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@306 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

-Fixed a problem at the implementation of method containsPlainVariable() in AbstractVariable subclasses. -Added a progress bar for the identification of type checking code smells. -Fixed the extraction of object references which are fields, parameters, or local variables whose declaration statement does not belong to slice nodes. In such a case, the extracted method should have a void return type and not contain a return statement. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@305 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The identification of Long Method code smells can now be performed on a whole Java Project, a specific Package of a project, a specific Compilation Unit, a specific Type (along with its nested types), and a specific Method of a type by selecting the appropriate element on the Package Explorer. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@304 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The rule regarding duplicated slice nodes containing a class instantiation for a specific reference has been strengthened. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@303 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Fixed a bug in alias analysis. The true control flow of do-while loops should not be visited in order to avoid infinite recursion. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@302 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Switch statement is fully supported in the construction of control flow and program dependence graphs. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@301 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

-Added support for Alias Analysis. -An additional rule has been added regarding slice extraction: A duplicated node of the slice containing a class instantiation for reference r, should not a data dependence to a removable node that either affects the state of r or assigns r to another reference. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@300 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
After the disposal of a ViewPart its SelectionListener must be removed. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@299 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Fixed the problem of identifying the already existing inheritance hierarchy which is associated with type-checking code performing RTTI by comparing named constants with the returned value of an abstract method invocation. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@298 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The dialog appearing before the application of Replace Type Code with State/Strategy refactoring, also checks if a type name has the same name with a class of java.lang package. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@297 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

-The dialog appearing before the application of Replace Type Code with State/Strategy refactoring, was enriched by giving the option to the user to rename the default abstract State/Strategy class name which was automatically generated based on the name of the state variable. -In Move Method refactoring, the access modifier of the source class is set to public, when source class type is passed as parameter to the moved method. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@296 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Before the application of Replace Type Code with State/Strategy refactoring, a dialog was added that gives the option to the user to rename the default class names which were automatically generated based on the names of the corresponding named constants. The dialog checks for the validity of the type names and also if a type name already exists in the source code of the project under examination. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@295 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Added support for renaming the default class name of concrete States corresponding to named constants. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@294 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Fixed a serious bug which caused an exception in the identification process after the application, undo, or redo of a refactoring. The CompilationUnit caching mechanism should be cleared after any operation that modifies the AST state (i.e. refactoring application, undo, redo operations, or even manual source code modification). git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@293 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Added three additional rules regarding the union of object slices which are related with duplicated statements. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@292 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Added three additional rules regarding the union of object slices. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@291 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Added initial support for object slicing. The rules regarding the union of object slices should be further investigated. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@290 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

An additional rule has been added: The statements which are duplicated in both the remaining and the extracted method should not contain any class instance creation or array creation. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@289 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Minor fixes in MANIFEST.MF git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@288 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Method NodeFinder.perform(ASTNode root, int start, int length) has significantly better performance compared to method NodeFinder.perform(ASTNode root, int start, int length, ITypeRoot source) git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@287 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The invocation of method hashCode() over ASTInformation objects caused a significant deterioration of performance. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@286 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

AST information is no longer permanently stored in memory. Instead, a caching mechanism is employed that enables the recovery and processing of AST information using temporary memory storage. This revision is compatible with Eclipse 3.5 Galileo. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@285 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Fixed a NullPointer exception. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@284 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

A Preference page has been added that can be used to reduce the number of reported Slice Extraction refactoring suggestions by adjusting various threshold values. The thresholds are related with the size of the slices and the degree of statement duplication caused by each suggestion. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@283 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The subclass types which are returned by the search engine should not be equal to the corresponding super type, in order to avoid infinite recursion. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@282 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Fixed a bug associated with the import declaration of types which are right operands in instanceof expressions. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@281 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Fixed the problem of leaving empty if/else or if/else if structures after the extraction of slice unions. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@280 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

- Fixed a bug concerning the handling of self-associations which caused an infinite loop when a method invoked itself through a self-association field. - When an abstract method is invoked through a superclass
reference and it is not possible to recover the actual
subclass type by static analysis, then all the methods
of the corresponding subclasses implementing it are
included in the Def/Use analysis.

- A progress bar has been added for the identification
process of Extract Method refactoring opportunities.

git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@279 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
additional code to revision 277 git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@278 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

-The fields which are accessed by the slice statements are not passed as parameters to the extracted method. -The invocation of the extracted method is placed before the first statement of the slice and not before the leader node of the corresponding boundary block. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@277 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The data dependency and anti-dependency edges which are carried by a loop node that does not belong to the block-based region are excluded from backward slicing traversal, even if both source and destination nodes belong to the block-based region. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@276 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The source code of invoked methods belonging to external library/API classes is also analyzed in order to produce more precise slices. The results of the analysis are stored and reused in an efficient manner. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@275 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The slice extraction refactoring opportunities are sorted in ascending order according to the ratio of duplicated statements to extracted statements. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@274 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The preview of the changes in Extract Method refactoring has been improved. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@273 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Fixed a minor bug that did not allow the execution of the final else case in the conditional. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@272 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The references through which fields are modified are not added to the set of defined variables. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@271 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Added support for calculating slices of composite variables git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@270 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The loop corresponding to loop-carried data dependencies and anti-dependencies is now provided. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@269 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
A rule involving loop-carried anti-dependencies has been added git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@268 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

-Added a new column in the Long Method view showing the ratio of duplicated statements to extracted statements. -The method invocations through field references are also
being handled.

git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@267 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Improvement of maintainability of the PDGNode inheritance hierarchy by extracting a fragment of duplicated code as a separate method in the subclasses and pulling up the common method in the superclass. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@266 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The definition of variable in the Program Dependence Graph has been extended to represent composite variables that consists of several parts. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@265 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The Def/Use analysis of method invocations has been extended to cover object references that are passed as parameters to the corresponding methods. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@264 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The definition of variable in the Program Dependence Graph has been extended in order to support data members(fields) which are accessed or modified through different object references having the same class type. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@263 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

- Optimized the implementation of forward reachable blocks by storing the forward reachable blocks for each block (when they are calculated for the first time), so that they won't have to recalculated. - Fixed the problem of infinite loops when examining
methods that invoke each other.

git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@262 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The method invocations through field references are analyzed in order to get information about the fields being modified or accessed inside the body of the corresponding methods (in addition to the method invocations through local variable references). Moreover, the direct modification of fields through local variable or field references are taken into account. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@261 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The method invocations whose class origin belongs to the system under examination are analyzed in order to get information about the fields being modified or accessed inside the body of the corresponding methods. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@260 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination bug fixed: The algorithm that identifies additional states for a specific type-checking code fragment (based on the common states that exist among all type-checking code fragments) has been improved. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@259 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

A subset of methods belonging to classes of Collections API are handled as methods that change the internal state of the objects from which they are being referenced. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@258 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Fixed a bug in the application of Extract Method refactoring concerning the handling of do loops. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@257 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The rule involving anti-dependencies has been updated. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@256 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Anti-dependence edges have been added to the Program Dependence Graph in order to support a new rule for behavior preservation. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@255 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Fixed a bug concerning the handling of try statements in calculation of the immediately nested nodes in branch nodes. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@254 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Two additional rules for checking the validity of the Program Dependence Graph slices have been introduced. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@253 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The handling of consecutive and nested try statements in the construction of control flow graph has been improved. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@252 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

- Fixed a bug concerning the handling of try statements in the construction of control flow graph. - Fixed a bug in the application of Extract Method refactoring. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@251 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The union of static slices based on common boundary blocks has been introduced. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@250 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The rules for excluding some program dependence slices have been updated. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@249 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Fixed a bug concerning the identification of the join nodes corresponding to conditional nodes. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@248 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Optimized the calculation of dominated blocks, so that they are calculated only once for the method entry node and the branch nodes. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@247 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Fixed a problem in the determination of indispensable nodes git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@246 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Extract Method refactoring has been completed. The original method is properly modified in order to invoke the extracted method. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@245 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The code smell Large Method has been introduced into the tool. The refactoring Extract Method has been implemented from scratch in order to work with slices from the Program Dependence Graph of a given method. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@244 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The defined and used variables of the program dependence nodes are now extracted as VariableDeclaration objects in order to be able to get their AST types. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@243 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Fixed an infinite loop bug in the backward traversal that is used to extract the slice nodes. The parameters that should be passed in the extracted method are also determined. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@242 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Loop-carried dependences are also included in the data dependences of the Program Dependence Graph. The parameters of the method are also included in the data dependence analysis. Class PDGSlice represents a block-based slice. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@241 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The Program Dependence Graph now supports the data dependences between the statements of a method concerning local variables. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@240 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Each node in the Program Dependence Graph contains information about the defined and used local variables. The defined variables refer to both variable declarations and variable assignments. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@239 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The Program Dependence Graph now supports the control dependences between the statements of a method. The Program Dependence Graph also supports the identification of: a) the dominated blocks for a given block b) the boundary blocks for a given statement git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@238 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The immediately nested nodes of the branch nodes are identified from the AST. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@237 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
This is a NullPointerException fix to previous revision 235 git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@236 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Fixed a bug concerning the identification of the join nodes corresponding to conditional nodes. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@235 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Class CFGBranchNode has been inherited by three subclasses. Subclass CFGBranchConditionalNode has as property the join node to which the corresponding conditional node ends. Subclass CFGBranchLoopNode supports the extraction of the immediately nested nodes by implementing abstract method getImmediatelyNestedNodes(). git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@234 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The construction of the control flow graph of a method is now supported. Currently, the statements being handled are: - While, For, For-each, Do-While - If, If-Else-If The remaining statements that will be handled are:
- Switch
- Break, Continue, Return
- Try/Catch, Throw

git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@233 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: If the field holding the current state is explicitly initialized with the value of a named constant, then it is initialized with an instance creation of the subclass corresponding to the specific named constant after the application of Replace Type Code with State/Strategy refactoring. If the field holding the current state is implicitly
initialized (i.e. its field declaration does not have an
initializer), then it is initialized with an instance
creation of the subclass corresponding to the named
constant which has the zero value after the application of
Replace Type Code with State/Strategy refactoring.

git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@232 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: The assignments of fields having +=, -=, *=, /=, %=, &=, |=, ^=, <<=, >>= and >>>>= as operator are properly handled. The prefix and postfix expressions having a field as operand and ++, -- as operator are properly handled. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@231 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The TypeCheckCodeFragmentAnalyzer also considers as assignments the Prefix and Postfix expressions which have increment or decrement operator. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@230 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The class that directly or indirectly extend "junit.framework.TestCase" or contain at least one method with @Test annotation are automatically excluded from the analysis. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@229 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
When the user selects a specific package to be analyzed, its subpackages are also included in the analysis. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@228 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The calculation of Entity Placement metric for the suggested Move Method refactorings has been optimized, by recalculating only the minimum required number of distances. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@227 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Type Check Elimination bug fixed: This is a fix to previous revision 225 git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@226 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination bug fixed: The handling of accessed static fields inside the type-checking code fragment has been improved. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@225 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Replace Type Code with State/Strategy refactoring employs CreateCompilationUnitChange in order to create the compilation units corresponding to the created State/Strategy inheritance hierarchy and delete the created compilation units when undo is performed. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@224 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

All implemented refactorings now extend class "org.eclipse.ltk.core.refactoring.Refactoring" in order to provide undo/redo support in the refactoring history of Eclipse. A refactoring wizard has been added that enables the preview of the changes before the application of the refactoring. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@223 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The tooltip indicating a dependency between two refactoring suggestions has been enhanced. It contains a link that selects the row of the suggestion corresponding to the dependency when it is pressed by the user. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@222 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Type Check Elimination bug fixed: This is a fix to previous revision 220 git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@221 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: If fields from the superclass of Context are accessed/assigned inside the type-checking branches, their accesses/assignments are replaced with the corresponding getter/setter method invocations through the Context parameter reference. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@220 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination precondition added: - The type-checking code fragment should not contain super method invocations. - The named constants that participate in the type-checks should belong to classes of the system and not library or API classes. Type Check Elimination functionality added:
The user can also select a specific package from the Package
Explorer to be analyzed.


git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@219 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: Replace Type Code with State/Strategy refactoring application creates an intermediate class in the case where more than one static fields correspond to the same type-checking code branch git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@218 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: Major changes have been made to support the handling of compound if statement infix expressions with conditional OR operators (||). git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@217 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination precondition added: The type-checking code fragment should not contain break or continue statements that do not belong inside the body of an iteration statement (for, while, do-while, enhanced for). git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@216 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

If a "this" expression exists in the arguments of a method invocation or class instance creation, it is replaced with the parameter of the polymorphic method corresponding to Context class. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@215 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Method modifiers() from BodyDeclaration returns a list of IExtendedModifier objects, which can either be Annotation or Modifier objects. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@214 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: The sorting mechanism of the refactoring suggestions has been improved so that the suggestions belonging to the same group appear consecutively. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@213 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: The type-check elimination opportunities are sorted according to their impact on the design of the system under study using the following criteria: 1) The number of cases that are going to utilize the same inheritance hierarchy at system level. 2) The number of cases that are going to utilize the same inheritance hierarchy at class level. 3) The average number of statements per state. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@212 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination bug fixed: The superclass type reference can also be obtained from a method invocation. If the invoker of a method invocation is the superclass type reference itself (without having a casting to the actual subclass type), then it should be also removed (or replaced with a this expression). git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@211 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Type Check Elimination bug fixed: This is a fix to previous revision 209 git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@210 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination bug fixed: If the invoker of a method invocation is a cast expression that casts the superclass type reference to the actual subclass type, then it should be removed. Moreover, the superclass type reference should not be passed as parameter to the polymorphic method. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@209 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Progress Monitor has been added to the identification of Feature Envy bad smells. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@208 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: When the current state is obtained through the invocation of a getter method of another class, the getter invocation is passed as argument to the invocation of the special method that creates the appropriate state subclass. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@207 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: The cases where the current state is obtained through a method invocation are now properly handled. The invoked method can be a getter method of another class, or an abstract method that polymorphically returns an integer value corresponding to the current state. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@206 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: - If the existing inheritance hierarchy belongs to a package which is different from the package that the Context class belong to, the import declarations corresponding to the inheritance hierarchy are added to the Context class. - The accessed static fields inside the type-checking code fragment are now properly handled. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@205 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination bug fixed: The modified/created setter method of the type field should have a default case that assigns the null literal to the type field. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@204 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: Fixed the problem of identifying the appropriate inheritance hierarchy when multiple inheritance trees have been already created from different static fields having the same names. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@203 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: The type-checking code fragments from all system classes are examined whether they perform type-checking on common static fields, in order to identify all the states related with each other. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@202 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: - Enumerated types are now supported. - The number of cases/branches in a type-checking code fragment should be more than one, or equal to one provided that a default case/final else branch exists. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@201 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination bug fixed: The identification of the returned variable corresponding to a type-checking code fragment has been improved. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@200 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
NullPointerException is fixed git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@199 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
The identification of Feature Envy bad smells can also be performed on specific packages of a project. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@198 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The algorithm for the extraction of refactoring suggestions takes into account conceptual bindings between the candidate target classes and the parameters of the method to be moved. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@197 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination bug fixed: The remaining If statement expressions are now analyzed for accessed local variables, fields and methods (of the Context class). git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@196 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Move Method Refactoring bug fixed: Recursive/self method invocations of the moved method inside its body are now properly handled. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@195 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The calculation of the Entity Placement metric corresponding to a Move Method refactoring suggestion is performed without cloning the system under study. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@194 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Move Method Refactoring functionality added: If the argument of a method invocation (through which the moved method should be invoked) is a cast expression, then it is parenthesized when placed as invoker. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@193 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

The algorithm for the extraction of Extract and Move Method candidate refactorings has been improved (all target objects that satisfy the preconditions are examined according to the number of member accesses and the distance from target class). git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@192 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: The detection of inheritance hierarchies has been updates in order to support inheritance trees that contain interfaces. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@191 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination bug fixed: The switch cases that do not contain break or return statements are properly handled. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@190 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination preconditions added: - The type-check branches should not contain assignments of local variables. - In the case of Replace Type Code with State/Strategy, the type variable should have int type. - In the case of Replace Conditional with Polymorphism, the type variable should not have java.lang.Object type. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@189 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: Runtime Type Identification by comparing the runtime class of an object (using getClass() method) with a Type Literal (Type.class) is officially supported. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@188 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: The methods that create the appropriate subclass object according to the int value of the passed parameter are excluded from being suggested. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@187 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: Additional subclasses that do not participate in the type-checking code fragment are also searched within SwitchCase expressions where the typeField or typeLocalVariable is the expression of the corresponding Switch statement. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@186 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: If the type field is found in the arguments of a method invocation, it is replaced with an invocation of the type field getter method. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@185 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: The case where multiple code fragments of the same method perform type-checking on the same type local variable is properly handled. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@184 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
Type Check Elimination bug fixed: The switch cases that do not contain statements are properly handled. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@183 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: The user has the ability to change the default name of the abstract method. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@182 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination bug fixed: Method modifyVariableInstructionsInSubclass() has been modified to handle remainingIfStatementExpressions which do not provide Binding support. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@181 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination bug fixed: Complex IfStatement infix expressions with more than one candidate type variables are now properly handled. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@180 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination optimized: Method modifyVariableInstructionsInSubclass() has been modified to take advantage of Bindings. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@179 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

Type Check Elimination functionality added: - The identification of CastExpressions that cast the typeField or typeLocalVariable to a subclass type has been improved. - The expression of the switch statements (not belonging
to the typeCheckCodeFragment) that access the typeField

A method is considered as delegate, if it contains only one statement of the following format: [return] expression.methodInvocation(arguments); where expression can be: 1) A field access (the field must be a member of the class that the delegate method belongs to) 2) A parameter access of the delegate method 3) A getter method invocation (the returned field must be a member of the class that the delegate method belongs to) 4) A "this" expression The existence of expression is not obligatory. If it does not exist, then the method delegates to another method of the same class. The arguments of the method invocation do not have any restrictions. git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@157 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb

A method should not contain a chain of method invocations to be considered as delegate. In order to move a method from source class to target class two conditions must hold: 1. The distance of method from target class should be lower than its distance from source class. 2. The number of entities accessed from target class should be greater than or equal to the number of entities accessed from source class. (The methods that are moved together with the source method are not taken into account in the entities accessed from source class) git-svn-id: svn://java.uom.gr/jdeodorant@78 b7e68eb2-82c8-4b8b-a2e2-35572869c0fb
